{"id":"259428462_Note_on_the_Smallest_Root_of_the_Independence_Polynomial","abstract":"One can define the independence polynomial of a graph G as follows. Let ik(G) denote the number of independent sets of size k of G, where i0(G)=1. Then the independence polynomial of G is I(G,x)=∑\nk=0\n\nn\n(−1)\nk\n\ni\n\nk\n\n(G)xk\n. In this paper we give a new proof of the fact that the root of I(G,x) having the smallest modulus is unique and is real.","authors":["Peter Csikvari"],"meta":["January 2013Combinatorics Probability and Computing 22(01)","DOI:10.1017/S0963548312000302"],"references":["250703313_The_independence_polynomial_of_a_graph-A_survey","322902469_The_Number_of_Words_of_Length_n_in_a_Graph_Monoid","264968784_On_clique_polynomials","262251996_The_Number_of_Words_of_Length_n_in_a_Graph_Monoid","243770212_Problemes_Combinatoires_de_Commutation_et_Rearrangements","233871590_The_Clique_Density_Theorem","229806929_Lower_bounds_on_the_number_of_triangles_in_a_graph","227272823_The_Repulsive_Lattice_Gas_the_Independent-Set_Polynomial_and_the_Lovsz_Local_Lemma","222673441_Clique_polynomials_have_a_unique_root_of_smallest_modulus","222278978_Dependence_polynomials","220357930_On_the_Minimal_Density_of_Triangles_in_Graphs","220357908_On_Dependency_Graphs_and_the_Lattice_Gas","220188307_Bounds_on_the_largest_root_of_the_matching_polynomial","2559708_Analytic_Combinatorics","1769807_The_number_of_cliques_in_graphs_of_given_order_and_size"]}